As a vocabulary is the sheet-anchor of a beginner's Vir-gil, great care has been taken to make this accurate, adequate, and easy to use. It has not been made an occasion or excuse for philological display From the immense mass of mate- rial which it might contain has been selected what we believe to be the maximum which the pupil of the secondary school will be able to utilize.
